  "body": "### Description\n\nI tend to run a lot of quarkus dev instances on my machine and its a bit tedious having to manually find a free debug port.\r\n\r\nWe already check debug port and print \"Port 5005 in use, not starting in debug mode\"  (in core/deployment/src/main/java/io/quarkus/deployment/dev/QuarkusDevModeLauncher.java) - couldn't we have a magic value like -1 or 0 to indicate \"pick one\" or a explicit flag to let quarkus dev try first on the configured port but if not free pick a random port and print it out.\r\n\r\nThen user can either manually or using IDE's attach features figure connect to the process without having to stop, adjust flag, start again.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
